parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially during inclement weather.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop working or work intermittently
often in rainy or wet conditions
obstructing the driver's view. In some cases
the wipers may only work when turned on high or when the motor is tapped or the wiper arm is pulled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration of the outside mirrors can cause distortion of vision, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The outside mirrors vibrate
causing distortion of vision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause a sudden loss of braking, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop or has extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, accidents, or extended stopping distance.
symptoms: ABS light illuminates
brakes lock up
vehicle skids or pulls to one side
extended stopping distance
growling noise from under the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master brake cylinder can cause a sudden loss of braking, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop or has extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on brake pads can cause reduced braking performance, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Brake pads wear out quickly
vehicle pulls to one side when braking
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat frame can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries. It can also cause discomfort, distraction, and anxiety for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The seat moves freely
the seat back collapses
the seat reclines unexpectedly
the seat slides forward or backward
the seat is loose and moves from side to side
the seat anchor breaks
the seat frame cracks or breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat track can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries. It can also cause discomfort, distraction, and anxiety for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The seat does not lock into track
the seat slides forward or backward
the seat moves intermittently
the seat pulls against the seat and shoulder belts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power seat can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries. It can also cause discomfort, distraction, and anxiety for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The power seat frame breaks
the seat rocks back and forth
the seat reclines unexpectedly.
